      "content_status": "source-backed draft",
      "source_status": "source links added",
      "markdown": "# Cooling And Power\n\n## What\n\nThis topic covers how a device stays powered and stays cool.\n\nIt includes power supplies, adapters, batteries, fans, heatsinks, and the basic idea that heat and power problems can look like many other faults.\n\n## Why\n\nCooling and power issues are common and easy to misread.\n\nIf a learner jumps too quickly to a deep fix, they can miss the safer first check.\n\n## How\n\n- Check whether the device powers on.\n- Confirm whether the charger, outlet, or battery path is working.\n- Look for fan noise, blocked vents, or obvious heat symptoms.\n- Treat the simplest visible cause first.\n\nSources:\n\n- CompTIA A+ Core 1 public overview: [CompTIA A+ Core 1 (V15)](https://www.comptia.org/en/certifications/a/core-1-and-2-v15/)\n\nChecklist:\n\n- [x] Create the cooling-and-power page shell.\n- [ ] Add a power-path diagram.\n- [ ] Add a fan and vent visual cue.\n- [x] Link the relevant troubleshooting activity.\n\nPractice\n\n- [Start Connector Match](../../app/index.html#module=drag)\n"
