      "source_status": "source links added",
      "markdown": "# System Memory\n\n## What\n\nSystem memory is RAM.\n\nIt is the short-term workspace the computer uses while programs are running.\n\n## Why\n\nRAM is one of the easiest parts to identify in the lab, and it has a useful mental model: if the device is working slowly, memory is one of the things a learner should think about, but not blindly replace.\n\n## How\n\n- Describe RAM as working memory.\n- Show where RAM usually sits on the board.\n- Teach safe handling by the edges.\n- Connect the part to performance symptoms and upgrade choices.\n\nSources:\n\n- CompTIA A+ Core 1 public overview: [CompTIA A+ Core 1 (V15)](https://www.comptia.org/en/certifications/a/core-1-and-2-v15/)\n\nChecklist:\n\n- [x] Create the system-memory page shell.\n- [ ] Add a RAM-stick visual.\n- [ ] Add a safe-handling note.\n- [x] Link the laptop memory practice activity.\n\nPractice\n\n- [Start Connector Match](../../app/index.html#module=drag)\n"
