      "markdown": "# Storage Device\n\n## What\n\nStorage devices keep files and installed software after power is off.\n\nIn the course sequence, this covers SSDs, HDDs, SATA, and M.2-level concepts at the learner-friendly service level.\n\n## Why\n\nStorage is a common exam and lab topic because it connects physical parts to symptoms like slow startup, missing files, and boot problems.\n\n## How\n\n- Compare shape and connector style.\n- Explain where the device sits in the system.\n- Tie the part to common symptoms.\n- Keep the lesson focused on recognition and first-step troubleshooting.\n\nSources:\n\n- CompTIA A+ Core 1 public overview: [CompTIA A+ Core 1 (V15)](https://www.comptia.org/en/certifications/a/core-1-and-2-v15/)\n\nChecklist:\n\n- [x] Create the storage-device page shell.\n- [ ] Add a SATA-versus-M.2 visual.\n- [ ] Add a slow-startup symptom note.\n- [x] Link the storage comparison activity.\n\nPractice\n\n- [Start Connector Match](../../app/index.html#module=drag)\n"
